# MEF Portal – Enterprise Plan vs Reality Gap (April 2026)

What's **actually in the codebase today** compared to every item in `ENTERPRISE_DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md`.

---

## ✅ Already Built (100% done)

| Plan Item | Where |
|---|---|
| Auth (login, logout, register) | `app/auth/routes.py` |
| Multi-level approval (Mentor → Advisor → HOD) | `app/staff/routes.py` |
| Request status tracking | `app/main/routes.py` `/status` |
| PDF generation (approved + bulk download) | `app/main/routes.py` `/download_approved`, `/download_status` |
| Student dashboard with stats | `app/main/routes.py` `/dashboard` |
| Role-based access control (RBAC) | All blueprints + security headers in `__init__.py` |
| Unified request form (Leave, OD, Apology, Bonafide, Permission) | `/unified_request` |
| Password hashing & validation | `app/auth/routes.py` `_verify_password` |
| Account lockout (5 attempts → 15-min lock) | `app/auth/routes.py` `_record_failed_attempt` |
| Rate limiting on all sensitive routes | `@limiter.limit(...)` decorators |
| CSRF protection (Flask-WTF) | `app/extensions.py` + `app/__init__.py` |
| Security response headers (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame, etc.) | `app/__init__.py` `@after_request` |
| Input sanitisation (Bleach) | All POST handlers |
| Leave limit enforcement (monthly cap) | `/unified_request` PostgreSQL `generate_series` query |
| Profile management (edit profile + change password) | `app/auth/routes.py` `/profile` |
| User management (HOD/Admin CRUD) | `app/staff/routes.py` |
| Leave rules (HOD can set per-dept limits) | `LeaveLimitRule` ORM — just fixed today |
| Health check endpoint `/healthz` | `app/main/routes.py` |
| Push subscription saving (PWA) | `/save-subscription` |
| Supabase/PostgreSQL connection via env vars | `config.py` |
| 76 passing automated tests | `tests/` (auth, main, staff, utils, security) |
| Logging (`logging.getLogger('mefportal')`) | All route files |
| gunicorn in requirements.txt | `requirements.txt` |
| SQLAlchemy 2.0 ORM models | `app/models.py` |
| Error handlers (404, 500, 403) | `app/__init__.py` |

